  "texts": [
    "It is not easy to get two independent views to merge the decision of the final prorate labels.",
    "Hence, graph-based methods are used for semi-supervised learning [8][9][10][11], which uses graphs to represent the data, where nodes represent samples and edges represent similarities between samples.",
    "Labels are propagated from labelled to unlabeled nodes based on the graph structure.",
    "However, the performance in this method is highly dependent on the graph's quality and structure; constructing and processing large graphs can be computationally expensive.",
    "Also, pseudo-labelling semi-supervised learning involves assigning pseudo-labels to the unlabeled data using the current model and then re-training the model using these pseudo-labels [12][13][14]."
  ],
